fields.description:
Export data from Jira into a CSV file suitable for ingestion by the See Scrum application.   This is a first step toward automated integration via web service.

Follow these step which created the attached csv:

# select Issues in left hand Nav
# select Advanced Search on right near Top
# select Switch to JQL link at right of the query fields
# Verify that the JQL displays all fields like this:  project = "SS" ORDER BY created DESC
# Select Export at Top right
# Select Export XML 
# Right click in Chrome to Save file as jira.xml
# Upload xml file to [https://www.freeformatter.com/xml-to-json-converter.html#ad-output|https://www.freeformatter.com/xml-to-json-converter.html#ad-output] 
# Press convert to json
# scroll down and press Copy to Clipboard and save in a new json file

fields.description:
* Create a Git project to maintain the source code for See Scrum.  
* Back up See Scrum project
* Validate that development and pull request round trip works for the web project
* Add the python server to the git repo
* Rename ScrumSee to SeeScrum 
* Merge develop branch into master after a full test

*GET LATEST*
git checkout develop
git fetch origin
git pull origin develop

*MAKE A CHANGE*
git branch my-chart
git checkout my-chart
git status
Develop changes

*CHECK IN THE CHANGE*
git add .
git commit -m 'feat: my chart'
git checkout develop
git pull origin develop
git merge --no-ff my-chart
git push origin develop

*DISCARD LOCAL CHANGES*

{noformat}git fetch --all
git reset --hard origin/develop{noformat}

*Merge develop BRANCH TO master*

{noformat}(on branch development)$ git merge master
(resolve any merge conflicts if there are any)
git checkout master 
git merge development
git push -u origin master{noformat}

fields.description:

* Use object model which leverages classes for at least a bar chart and an SVG class
* Committed and completed with a big trend line going to a box with the insight.   The insight should include a Reliability Index which equals 100 * (completed/committed)

* Measure by
** Story Points (Default)
** Hours
** Stories
** LOC
** Pull Requests
** Jira Releases

fields.description:
Get data with the REST service at this [link|https://developer.atlassian.com/server/jira/platform/rest-apis/?_ga=2.170388647.640047974.1597074713-1787544790.1596981785]

Jira Cloud REST API:  [https://docs.atlassian.com/jira-software/REST/latest/|https://docs.atlassian.com/jira-software/REST/latest/] 

[https://developer.atlassian.com/cloud/jira/platform/rest/v3/intro/#about|https://developer.atlassian.com/cloud/jira/platform/rest/v3/intro/#about]



*Allow Anonymous Access* 

This means no authentication.  Should allow anonymous access for read-only

[https://confluence.atlassian.com/adminjiracloud/allowing-anonymous-access-to-your-project-779172888.html|https://confluence.atlassian.com/adminjiracloud/allowing-anonymous-access-to-your-project-779172888.html]

*Authenticate with a Json Web Token (JWT)* 

[https://jonathanmh.com/example-json-web-tokens-vanilla-javascript/|https://jonathanmh.com/example-json-web-tokens-vanilla-javascript/]

{{Base URL for all APIs: https://seescrum.atlassian.net/rest/api/3}}

*APIs to Use*

* [https://docs.atlassian.com/jira-software/REST/7.3.1/#agile/1.0/board/\{boardId}/epic-getEpics|https://docs.atlassian.com/jira-software/REST/7.3.1/#agile/1.0/board/%7BboardId%7D/epic-getEpics]
* [https://docs.atlassian.com/jira-software/REST/7.3.1/#agile/1.0/epic-getEpic|https://docs.atlassian.com/jira-software/REST/7.3.1/#agile/1.0/epic-getEpic]
* [https://docs.atlassian.com/jira-software/REST/7.3.1/#agile/1.0/board/\{boardId}/epic-getIssuesForEpic|https://docs.atlassian.com/jira-software/REST/7.3.1/#agile/1.0/board/%7BboardId%7D/epic-getIssuesForEpic]
* [https://docs.atlassian.com/jira-software/REST/7.3.1/#agile/1.0/board/\{boardId}/epic-getIssuesWithoutEpic|https://docs.atlassian.com/jira-software/REST/7.3.1/#agile/1.0/board/%7BboardId%7D/epic-getIssuesWithoutEpic]



* [https://docs.atlassian.com/jira-software/REST/7.3.1/#agile/1.0/issue-getIssue|https://docs.atlassian.com/jira-software/REST/7.3.1/#agile/1.0/issue-getIssue]



* [https://docs.atlassian.com/jira-software/REST/7.3.1/#agile/1.0/board/\{boardId}/sprint-getAllSprints|https://docs.atlassian.com/jira-software/REST/7.3.1/#agile/1.0/board/%7BboardId%7D/sprint-getAllSprints]
* [https://docs.atlassian.com/jira-software/REST/7.3.1/#agile/1.0/sprint-getSprint|https://docs.atlassian.com/jira-software/REST/7.3.1/#agile/1.0/sprint-getSprint]
